{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# 1.0 release hygiene: dependabot, classifier bump, stability-promise flip, RC skip (tag signing: explicit skip)\n\n## Why\n\nFinal mechanical artifacts for the 1.0 declaration, sized to what 2026 peers actually do — which REVERSES two earlier assumptions. (1) Signed git tags are no longer convergent: of CPython/pip/ruff/uv/pytest/httpx, zero sign new release tags in 2026 (CPython dropped GPG at 3.14 per PEP 761; ruff/uv/httpx use lightweight tags); the baseline is annotated tags + GitHub immutable releases + PEP 740 attestations — all already in place here. (2) RC trains are not convergent: pydantic v2 shipped beta→final in 13 days with zero rcs; attrs/structlog skipped 1.0 entirely; the load-bearing artifact is the written compatibility policy, which `docs/api-stability.md` already is.\n\n## What\n\n- `.github/dependabot.yml`, the pip/pydantic minimal pattern: `github-actions` ecosystem ONLY, monthly, one catch-all group, `cooldown: default-days: 7`. **Finding-rejection note (a prior review claimed `cooldown` is not a Dependabot key — that is incorrect):** `cooldown` with `default-days` is a supported schema key, in production use verbatim in pip's own config (https://github.com/pypa/pip/blob/main/.github/dependabot.yml) and documented in GitHub's Dependabot options reference; cite both in the file's header comment so the next reviewer doesn't re-flag it. No `pip` ecosystem entry — version updates act on pins/lockfiles; rebar's unpinned `>=` core deps give them nothing but noise, and security ALERTS fire regardless of this file (rationale in header comments). Add a `uv` block only if a `uv.lock` is ever committed.\n- Staged for the v1.0.0 release change (landing vehicle = the release change itself, referenced from this ticket when pushed): bump `Development Status :: 4 - Beta` → `5 - Production/Stable` (pyproject classifier) and flip the pre-1.0 caveat in `docs/api-stability.md` so the stability matrix becomes the operative SemVer promise (the doc already anticipates this flip).\n- `docs/releasing.md` decision records:\n  - Tag signing: SKIPPED, with rationale (2026 peer baseline; attestations cover artifact provenance) and revisit triggers (workflow compromise entering the threat model, or a downstream consumer asking to verify tags). Confirm annotated tags remain the practice and immutable releases stay on.\n  - **RC: SKIPPED (the recorded decision, not an open option).** Rationale: an RC only yields data if someone runs it; with no external adopters, `--pre` installs ≈ 0 and `1.0.1` is the de-facto rc. Revisit trigger: an external adopter volunteering to test. **Conditional requirement recorded alongside (because today's release automation is RC-unsafe):** `release.yml` fires on ALL `v*` tags (line ~19), passes `--latest` unconditionally to `gh release create` (lines ~103/106), and runs the MCP-registry publish job — so a hypothetical `v1.0.0rc1` tag would be marked the Latest GitHub release AND published to the MCP registry. The releasing.md note must state: no rc-form tag may be pushed unless release.yml first gains a prerelease guard (detect `rc` in the tag → `--prerelease`, not `--latest`; skip the MCP-registry job). This story does NOT modify release.yml (no RC is planned); it makes the constraint impossible to trip over blindly.\n- Verify at execution: `git tag -l 'v*'` confirms no pre-existing rc-form tags contradict the note; PEP 440 spelling (`1.0.0rc1`, not `-rc.1`) is used in the constraint text.\n- Record explicit deferrals as non-goals in docs/releasing.md's decisions section: SBOM/license-scan tooling beyond GitHub's dependency-graph export; Renovate; a lockfile for optional extras (revisit post-1.0).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `.github/dependabot.yml`; docs/releasing.md decision records (tag signing, RC skip + guard constraint, deferrals); the classifier bump + api-stability flip STAGED and referenced (executed in the 1.0 release change).\nOUT: modifying release.yml; executing the release; contract-freeze code work (exit codes / error envelope / MCP schema pin — tracked elsewhere); SBOM tooling; CI matrix changes (Windows explicitly out — classifiers claim POSIX/macOS, consistent today).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `dependabot.yml` committed — prove: `test -f .github/dependabot.yml`; contains exactly one `package-ecosystem` entry (`github-actions`), `interval: monthly`, a catch-all group, `cooldown: default-days: 7`, and header comments carrying both the no-pip rationale and the cooldown citation.\n- [ ] Dependabot accepts the config — prove: after push, the repo's Dependabot tab / `gh api repos/navapbc/rebar/dependabot/alerts` shows no config-parse error (or the Insights → Dependency graph → Dependabot view shows the job scheduled).\n- [ ] docs/releasing.md contains: tag-signing skip + revisit triggers; RC-skip decision + the release.yml prerelease-guard constraint (naming `--latest` and the MCP-registry job as the specific hazards); the deferral list — prove: greps for \"tag signing\", \"1.0.0rc1\", \"--latest\", \"SBOM\".\n- [ ] Classifier bump + api-stability flip staged — prove: this ticket references the 1.0 release change (Gerrit change id or commit) that carries both edits, or a ticket comment records they are queued for it.\n- [ ] No rc-form tags exist — prove: `git tag -l | grep -c rc` = 0."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783631037453814001,"uuid":"16c5ead3-66ca-498b-bca7-f3638e524116"}